Perun Consultants is the leading independent advisory firm with offices in Hong Kong and Singapore. We specialise in provision of high quality services in the areas of forensic accounting, corporate advisory, restructuring, turnaround and liquidation appointments. At Perun, we promote a work-life balance, value individualism and embrace the differences.

We are currently seeking an ambitious and qualified candidate with the following attributes to join our Hong Kong office as a Forensic Accounting Manager / Assistant Manager / Associate:


Batchelor’s degree in Accounting, Finance, Computer Science, Information Technology, Law or other Business-related discipline preferred.
CA, CPA, ACCA or equivalent. Consideration will also be given to part qualified candidates, with support given to complete the qualification process;
4+ years relevant experience for the position of Assistant Manager and 2+ years relevant experience for the position of Associate.
• Eager to learn and motivated to succeed;
• Proficient in detailed financial and commercial analysis and be able to identify potential areas of sensitivity;
• Self-motivated, proactive and mature;
• Proficient in Microsoft office applications;
• Strong financial, business analytical and report writing skills; and
• Excellent written and oral communication skills in both English and Mandarin Chinese, including both technical and business writing.
The successful candidate will possess technical knowledge of financial accounting practices and be able to demonstrate experience (commensurate with the applicable employment grade) with the following:

Assessment and quantification of losses and potential damage awards;
Valuation and appraisal of assets;
Design and evaluation of financial forecast models;
Report writing;
Providing litigation support services, working closely with legal counsel, law enforcement officers and regulatory agencies; and
Assisting with internal and external investigations.
Insolvency-related experience; and
Assisting with internal and external investigations.

In addition to the above role, we are always interested in hearing from proactive, commercially minded, individuals at all levels of seniority and experience looking to work in a dynamic and flexible environment.

We offer a competitive remuneration package where you will be rewarded for your individual and team performance. We are committed to being an inclusive employer and are happy to consider flexible working arrangements.
To apply, contact us at Apply Now .

