To cope with the continuous growing business needs, we are actively looking for Senior Manager/Manager to join the Group financial and regulatory reporting team.

Key Responsibilities

Prepare and ensure month-end, quarter-end, interim and annual financial closing and reporting processes with good quality in a timely manner;
Liaise with finance teams of the Group’s subsidiaries and external auditors for any issues related to financial and accounting;
Participate in the property valuation matters;
Support the deliverables for the Audit Committee and the Board of Directors;
Provide analytical review on the consolidated financial results;
Work closely with IT department to support continuous process and system enhancements to drive efficiency and effectiveness of the closing process and  the production of deliverables;
Participate in the implementation of IFRS 9, IFRS 17, and other new accounting standards;
Achieve assigned functions accurately and efficiently;
Provide guidance and technical advice to subsidiaries;
Perform ad-hoc financial management tasks and duties as assigned.

 Requirements

Bachelor’s Degree in Accounting/Finance or above;
CPA or equivalent qualification is a MUST;
Min 10 (for Senior Manager)/ min 5 (for Manager) years strong and solid  experience in financial reporting from Big 4 or listed companies;
Solid experience in complex group consolidation preparation and group  financial reporting;
Excellent problem solving and analytical skills;
Excellent multi-tasking skills;
Strong communication skills in written and spoken English, Cantonese and Mandarin;
Strong leadership skills, sound business acumen and able to work under pressure;
Ability to support multi stakeholder information needs;
Proficiency in HFM, IFRS and PRC GAAP a plus;
Work in Hong Kong with occasional travelling to Mainland is required.

